# Post-gate checkout evidence captures live here at runtime.
#
# Convention:  store-data/checkout-captures/{shop_id}/{txn_ref}.jpg
#
#   - One image per APPROVED scan, written by POST /api/checkout/capture only
#     after the scan clears the verification gate (an HMAC capture token is
#     issued exclusively on gate-pass). Invalid/blocked scans never produce a
#     capture.
#   - Each write is checksum-verified (sha256, read back from disk) and the
#     resulting reference (path + checksum + timestamp) is bound to the
#     transaction state in Redis (txn:capture:{txn_ref}).
#   - Scoped per shop_id so captures never leak between tenants.
#
# The actual .jpg files are git-ignored (see .gitignore); this .gitkeep only
# preserves the directory + documents the convention in the repo.
